KW  - Trade bias measures
KW  - Export promotion
AB  - Many countries provide simultaneous incentives to import competing and export sectors. We show that if such policies are temporary they expand the traded goods sector and improve the current account. Furthermore, with learning-by-doing externalities in the traded goods sector, they can increase growth. We conclude that trade orientation cannot be determined by comparing incentives given to the import and export sectors at a point in time.
